            ; we <rs id="t18230115-90-viclabel504" type="occupation">keep a snuff shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230115-90-victim847 t18230115-90-viclabel504"></join> in <placeName id="t18230115-90-crimeloc505">Foley-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230115-90-crimeloc505" type="placeName" value="Foley-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230115-90-crimeloc505" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230115-90-off502 t18230115-90-crimeloc505"></join>. On the 14th of December, about ten o'clock in the morning, I was in the parlour, my servant came to me - I went into the shop, and found the till wide open, and a small drawer at the back of it gone; it was safe a few minutes before; there was a shilling in it, but how much more I do not know.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230115-90-person849">
                  GEORGE 
                  LUTZ
               <interp inst="t18230115-90-person849" type="surname" value="LUTZ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230115-90-person849" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230115-90-person849" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live next door but one to Walters. I stood at my door and saw the prisoner and another looking in at the window; I saw them go into the shop and run out again, I went to Mrs. Walters, who missed her drawer, and then followed the prisoner for half a mile, into Tottenham-court-road, and took him; he said, he did not take the money, but it was the other boy; that there was only one shilling, and the other boy had it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18230115-90-verdict506" type="verdictDescription">
